        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices for Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement error handling with retries for transient failures, using exponential backoff. Cache frequent requests, such as voice lists, to reduce latency. For streaming, use chunked transfer encoding and handle network interruptions gracefully. Secure your API keys with environment variables and rotate them regularly. Test with varied text inputs to ensure robustness against edge cases like special characters or long content."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Troubleshooting and Optimization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common issues include authentication errors (check key validity) and audio quality problems (adjust sample rate or voice settings). Use logging to track request/response cycles and identify bottlenecks. Optimize by batching synthesis requests where possible and monitoring latency metrics. For high-traffic scenarios, consider load balancing across multiple API keys and implementing circuit breakers to prevent cascade failures."
          }
        ]
      }
